snippet.textDisplay: Hello. How can I change output size when I use interactive corona render? I couldn't find it ever on settings and in tutorials.
snippet.textOriginal: Hello. How can I change output size when I use interactive corona render? I couldn't find it ever on settings and in tutorials.

snippet.textDisplay: @CoronaRenderer It helped. Thank you much.
snippet.textOriginal: @CoronaRenderer It helped. Thank you much.

snippet.textDisplay: If you are in Max, the VFB will pick a size to begin with based on the final render aspect ratio, but then you can simply drag the VFB window to whichever size you prefer same as resizing any window. Hope that helps! Tom
snippet.textOriginal: If you are in Max, the VFB will pick a size to begin with based on the final render aspect ratio, but then you can simply drag the VFB window to whichever size you prefer same as resizing any window. Hope that helps! Tom

snippet.textDisplay: Is there a setting options for it to use GPU rather then CPU for rendering? is there a tutorial video for it? Thanks
snippet.textOriginal: Is there a setting options for it to use GPU rather then CPU for rendering? is there a tutorial video for it? Thanks

snippet.textDisplay: Corona is CPU only, so there are no settings to use the GPU :) There are no plans to introduce GPU rendering at this time  - see https://corona-renderer.com/features/proudly-cpu-based . Thanks! Tom
snippet.textOriginal: Corona is CPU only, so there are no settings to use the GPU :) There are no plans to introduce GPU rendering at this time  - see https://corona-renderer.com/features/proudly-cpu-based . Thanks! Tom

snippet.textDisplay: For exterior shots, you have to adjust the exposure, usually done in the camera or the VFB tab. There is a section about that, it's mentioned at 3m 40s or so - exposure should be lowered to around -2 or -4 for exteriors. Thanks! Tom
